- 'Performance metrics' include the average temperature and the maximum candidate value;
- The average temperature setting is used to filter experiments, indicating a threshold for the experimental conditions;
- The maximum candidate value is used to rank the experiments, suggesting a focus on the best-performing experiments.

- "Garden of projects and models" refers to the collection of experiments conducted within different projects using various models;
- "Temperature setting" represents the environmental conditions or parameters used during the experiments;
- "Average performance" is the mean value of the performance metrics for each model.

- "soared to the highest peaks of success" refers to the experiments with the highest `best_value`;
- The `best_value` is a metric used to evaluate the performance of experiments in machine learning;
- The `top 10 experiments` are those with the highest `best_value` that are not null.

- 'Best Project' refers to the experiment with the highest candidate value within its project;
- 'Best Model' refers to the experiment with the highest candidate value for its specific model within the project;
- 'Other' refers to experiments that are not the best in either their project or model.

